file_content.text: Catastrophic reactor failure imminent.
Enough! I'm taking you with me whether you like it or not!
Reactor shutdown sequence initiated. Warning: grid integrity at risk.
Damn your stubbornness. You just gambled with the fate of the entire galaxy!
I took a calculated risk. It paid off.
It had to be done.
You engaged in an unsuccessful attempt to kill us both, is what you did.
I never said you had to stay. Come on.
Unbelievable.
You thought you were going to lose me.
[Flirt] You were worried.
Don't start. Let's just go.
It worked.
Deal with it.
That's hardly the--can we go now?
Primary grid shutdown protocols are in effect.
Hurry!
Relax. It's going to be fine.
Be calm.
It'll go quicker without distractions.
Quiet, Lana.
[Say nothing]
Relaxing didn't work so well! Now what do you propose to do?
What? What could you possibly intend to do?
Whatever I can.
Catastrophic reactor failure imminent.
There.
Catastrophic reactor failure imminent.
There's nothing we can do here. Let's go.
Don't you dare!
If that thing blows, it's taking a whole lot of people with it! You can still shut it down!
Half the city will go dark, but the countless thousands who live and work here will have a chance!
Do you see? This is how far they'll go to stop you. We need to get you offworld now!
If I let that reactor go, I'm not worth saving.
I have to stop it.
I won't save my own skin at the cost of others'.
I can't let them die.
I have a chance to minimize collateral damage. I'm taking it.
I'd rather save lives.
My ulcers have ulcers. Like I need this on my conscience.
Ugh, I can't live with that.
The masses cannot fear you if there are no masses.
Their deaths don't help me.
If I am to rule the galaxy, it will be with the most subjects, not the fewest.
They may one day be my people.
Those people out there, they've got nothing to do with this. I'm shutting it down.
They don't deserve this.
I have quite enough weighing on my conscience. I'm going to fix this.
I'm leaving with a clear mind.
Your slumber must have had quite an effect.
You'd better know what you're doing.
If what you've said about the Republic is true, we have to keep going.
We have bigger concerns.
Let this be on Vaylin's conscience, if she has one.
I didn't cause this. Let's go.
We've got bigger concerns than a single reactor. Let's move out.
We're staying on mission.
This is their mess. Come on, we're out of here.
It's not my problem.
This entire world can come apart as far as I'm concerned.
Let it all burn.
What kind of monster am I helping you liberate?
I won't let the Empire fall into ruin. It's time to leave this place.
My Empire needs me.
Sooner I'm off this rock, the better. Let's go.
We're gone.
Everyone will be responding to the meltdown. All the easier for us to slip away.
It will make good cover.
Damn it, Lana, those are people. My people!
All this was Vaylin's doing. If you have a problem, I suggest taking it up with her.
Don't think I won't.
Catastrophic reactor failure imminent.
It's going to rupture! Sound the evacuation, get everybody out! Ten blocks in every direction!
They'll never make it! Thousands... tens of thousands of people! There's no time!
We have to try! Go!
